I came up with this birthday cookie idea a few years ago for my husband’s 55th birthday.

Real life post today. 
I made these cookies for the doctors, nurses and staff at @nihgov for the spectacular care they have provided to my son, @joeybmyers 💙
Joey contracted an extremely rare, serious parasitic infection while on a trip to Costa Rica back in April. The last few months have been really challenging for him, filled with long days at NIH, bloodwork, scans, biopsies, you name it. Joey knows more than he ever wanted to know about wound care. Getting properly diagnosed and treated has pretty much taken up his life since May, but no complaints from this guy. He’s probably the most resilient person I have ever known. Many prayers have been said by many people for his recovery. I am most grateful for each and every one. THANK YOU for those prayers and for everyone at NIH for taking such good care of my son. 💙
